Backport of upstream PR #70 (rangermix/TwitchDropsMiner#70, capkz:fix/drops-spade-post-endpoint,
still unmerged): "restore drops progress by sending watch events via Spade POST".

Twitch removed the `sendSpadeEvents` GraphQL mutation during the 2026 Summer Drops event,
which silently froze all drop progress (the miner "watches" a channel but earns nothing —
upstream issue #69). This reverts watch-event reporting to a direct POST against the Spade
endpoint (beacon.twitch.tv). Drop this patch once upstream ships it in a release.

NOTE: drop crediting also requires beacon.twitch.tv to resolve — it is blocked by default on
tracker-blocking DNS (NextDNS) and must be allowlisted, or the POST goes to 0.0.0.0.

(channel.py hunks only — the PR's test-file change is not needed at runtime.)
